headlines.title: Jobs Report: Live Updates on U.S. Hiring in May
headlines.description: Economists expect the Labor Department’s monthly report to show that hiring proceeded at a healthy rate in May, with employers adding 125,000 jobs.

headlines.title: Billy Joel reveals suicide attempts after affair with friend's wife in documentary
headlines.description: Billy Joel revealed multiple suicide attempts, one of which left him in a coma, after having an affair with his friend's wife in a new documentary.

headlines.title: AI risks 'broken' career ladder for college graduates, some experts say
headlines.description: Advances of AI chatbots like ChatGPT heighten concern, experts say.

headlines.title: 7 senators to watch as Republicans make changes to Trump's big bill
headlines.description: From centrists worried about Medicaid cuts to conservative hard-liners demanding steeper spending reductions, Senate GOP leaders face a tricky balancing act.

headlines.title: Nintendo Switch 2
headlines.description: From consoles, to games and accessories, here's everything Switch 2 that's now available to buy.

headlines.title: Trump says it may be better to let Ukraine, Russia 'fight for a while'
headlines.description: In an Oval Office meeting with German Chancellor Friedrich Merz, President Trump likened the war between Russia and Ukraine to a fight between two children who hate each other.

headlines.title: Videos Show Chaos Around Israeli-Backed Gaza Food Sites
headlines.description: Danger and desperation are clear in imagery near the aid sites. Dozens of Palestinians were killed in at least two instances after Israeli troops opened fire near the sites.

headlines.title: Will White Men Rush to Court After Justices’ Latest Ruling? Not Likely.
headlines.description: The Supreme Court on Thursday made it easier for members of so-called majority groups to bring discrimination cases, but experts say the impact is likely to be limited.

headlines.title: Army preparing for largest military parade on the capital’s streets in decades, featuring 7 million pounds of hardware
headlines.description: Millions of pounds of military hardware are expected to roll down the US capital’s streets in less than two weeks, fulfilling a dream of President Donald Trump but also an effort that has sparked concerns about how the roads of Washington, DC, will fare under the literal weight of heavy tanks and fighting vehicles.

headlines.title: Judge puts temporary hold on Trump's latest ban on Harvard's foreign students
headlines.description: Admitted students around the world are anxiously tracking the school's feud with the Trump administration, which is seeking to keep it from enrolling international students.
